On Tue, 20 Aug 2002, Nikki Elko wrote:

> What could cause my bus (1973 high-roof camper, as stock as possible) to sound
> like I'm running snow tires or big 4x4 tires on the front at highway speeds?
>   Kind of a growly whirring road noise.
>
> I thought CVs grumbled from the rear (this sounds like it's in the front), and
> wheel bearings would make a squirrely noise.

Could be bearings, or it could be uneven tire wear.  How smooth are the
tires wearing.  If they're stepping or cupping it can sound like the
symptoms you describe.

